  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study will investigate whether dietary modification could provide positive effects on
      brain functions in elderly people with mild cognitive impairment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The age-related degradation of cognitive functions even to the point of neurodegenerative
      disorders such as Alzheimer`s disease are a growing public-health concern with devastating
      effects.

      Referring to animal data, empirical studies, and pilot human trials, dietary modification
      (caloric restriction, omega-3 fatty acids and resveratrol) should improve cognitive
      functions such as learning and memory. To test this hypothesis, the researchers study
      general brain functions in elderly subjects (50-80 years old) with mild cognitive
      impairment.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
